      {
        "conflict": "MJ proposed fixed-window counters (rate_limit:{api_key}:{window_start_unix} with TTL). Kobe flagged this allows 2x burst at window boundaries, violating Bird's 'rolling window' domain rule.",
        "resolution": "Adopt Kobe's recommendation: use Redis sorted sets for a true sliding window. This satisfies Bird's rolling-window requirement and eliminates the boundary burst. MJ's middleware placement and Redis-based approach are preserved; only the data structure changes."
      },
      {
        "conflict": "Pippen defined Retry-After as 'TTL of the current window key', which assumes MJ's fixed-window key design.",
        "resolution": "With sorted sets there is no per-window key TTL. Retry-After is instead computed as: ceiling((score_of_oldest_member_in_set + 60) - current_time). The intent (dynamic, not fixed) is preserved."
      }
    ],
    "open_questions": []
  },
